doc,<br><br>
So now we are hyenas? Notice when I said &quot;we&quot; I was not keeping a mouse in my pocket.<br><br>
I think that the dialogue has been such that we all have been able to form a decent perception of each other. Take what you want and let the rest slide.<br><br>
It is easy to get caught up in the slander and name calling - for my part I have had to make a conscious effort to refrain. <br><br>
The latest &quot;hyena&quot; term should serve as further notice  that you have taken it upon yourself to *separate yourself* from the others. This separation was not accomplished by your taking the moral highground as you might think. Rather, you denounce - blaming us because the site is not going in a certain direction.<br><br>
As for your anonymous posts, I learned a while back not to respond to anyone who is anonymous. The reasons are obvious to me.<br><br>
As long as I am part of this pack of hyenas, I will always insist that everyone have a seat at the table. All should be treated with respect. All opinions, whether I agree with them or not, or whether they are expressed by giraffes, aardvarks, or woodchucks, will be heard. That is the way I am and the way that I always will be.<br><br>

<p><code>-- wingman#greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


